# MongoDB Atlas Configuration
# Replace with your actual MongoDB Atlas connection string
# Get this from: https://cloud.mongodb.com/ -> Connect -> Connect your application

# Example format:
# MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@<cluster-name>.mongodb.net/<database-name>?retryWrites=true&w=majority"

# Your connection string should look like:
MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://your-username:your-password@your-cluster.mongodb.net/flashgenius_ai?retryWrites=true&w=majority"

# If you don't have MongoDB Atlas, you can:
# 1. Create a free account at https://cloud.mongodb.com/
# 2. Create a new cluster (free tier available)
# 3. Create a database user
# 4. Get the connection string
# 5. Replace the values above